    {
      "id": "598d82ae1bb2df6858522929e869601ab5a2b4b3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-20 13:58:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe changes for the second patch seem to be nothing to do with LU-372. They seem to be about not loading LLOOP and the remove of SKIP_LFSCK plus some other work.\r\n\r\nHave these been pushed accidently to this change.\r\n\r\nIf not then at least we should change the Jira and the comments to reflect the extra work. [In the description of the Jira not as an appended comment.]",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "3404d39390b7f92061b4dde54bb7435850f1fb45",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-21 07:37:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Verified\n\nHi Chris,\n\nThe replay-single test 61d failure described in LU-372 is not the same as those described in other JIRA tickets. It occurred while running the tests under combined MGS/MDS failover configuration and \"do_facet mgs\" did not figure out the correct active MGS node. The patch exactly fixed the issue.\n\nAlthough replay-single test 61d is currently in the ALWAYS_EXCEPT list on master branch, other tests which perform \"do_facet mgs\" would also likely hit the same issue under the failover configuration.\n\nHere are the recovery/failover test results after applying the patch on Lustre master build 2.0.65.0:\nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/7f371672-b281-11e0-b33f-52540025f9af\nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8be67002-b281-11e0-b33f-52540025f9af\nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9065630e-b281-11e0-b33f-52540025f9af\nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/55e697ca-b2cc-11e0-b33f-52540025f9af\nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1674750c-b35e-11e0-b33f-52540025f9af",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "dcb854574d5fb6c437dc2ae7c80d716cb9da2348",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-21 15:21:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nBut why changes to lfsck skips etc. I don't understand why these are part of this commit. Sorry.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "96372319cbd735a80e0b06cc318105be9f83d520",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-22 03:47:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n{quote}\n\nBut why changes to lfsck skips etc. I don't understand why these are part of this commit. Sorry.\n\n{quote}\n\nThe patch does not contain any changes to lfsck. Ah, I think you did a comparison between Patch Set 2 and 1.\n\nFor set 1, its parent is dea1dfaf (LU-376 Positive LL_DIR_END_OFF to indicate the tail of dir hash/offset). However, the parent for set 2 is fc73791d (LU-413 limit used inodes for performance tests). The changes on test-framework.sh between those two commits were all showed up while comparing set 2 with set 1, which made you confused.\n\nSo, could you please choose \"Base\" as the \"Old Version\" and review the change of Patch Set 2? It's a clean show, I think.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "cd9585aa99abd1553cc5a9459089e1bca70ead4c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-27 13:21:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nWow that is confusing!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7ca025ab94c0211490c77e2d096113f573bb9179",
